.Dd April 7, 2026
.Dt MOXYFILE 5
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm moxyfile
.Nd configuration file for moxy
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is the configuration file for
.Xr moxy 1 .
It uses TOML format and controls which child MCP servers are spawned,
how their capabilities are aggregated, and per-server behavior options
like ephemeral mode, annotation filtering, and pagination.
.Sh FILE HIERARCHY
Configuration files are loaded and merged in order:
.Bl -enum
.It
.Pa ~/.config/moxy/moxyfile
(global).
.It
Each parent directory between
.Ev HOME
and the current working directory.
.It
.Pa ./moxyfile
(project-local).
.El
.Pp
Later files override earlier ones.
Servers are matched by name: a same-named server in an overlay replaces
the base server entirely.
New servers from overlays are appended.
Top-level boolean flags are replaced if present in the overlay.
.Sh TOP-LEVEL KEYS
.Bl -tag -width "progressive-disclosure"
.It Va ephemeral
When set to
.Cm true ,
servers without an explicit
.Va ephemeral
setting are treated as ephemeral by default.
Optional.
Default:
.Cm false .
.It Va progressive-disclosure
When set to
.Cm true ,
enables progressive disclosure for servers without an explicit setting.
Optional.
Default:
.Cm false .
.El
.Sh SERVERS
Each server is defined as an array-of-tables entry:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[servers]]
name = "grit"
command = "grit mcp"
.Ed
.Ss Required fields
.Bl -tag -width "command"
.It Va name
Unique identifier for the server.
Must not contain dots
.Pq dots are used as the namespace separator .
May contain hyphens.
.It Va command
Shell command to spawn the server.
See
.Sx COMMAND FORMAT
below.
.El
.Ss Optional fields
.Bl -tag -width "progressive-disclosure"
.It Va ephemeral
When
.Cm true ,
the server is not kept running.
Moxy probes it at startup to discover capabilities, shuts it down,
and re-spawns it on demand for each tool call.
Overrides the global
.Va ephemeral
setting.
.It Va progressive-disclosure
Overrides the global
.Va progressive-disclosure
setting for this server.
.It Va paginate
When
.Cm true ,
enables cursor-based pagination for this server's resource lists.
Default:
.Cm false .
.It Va generate-resource-tools
When
.Cm true ,
generates synthetic
.Cm resource-read
and
.Cm resource-templates
tools for this server, allowing tool-only clients to access resources.
.It Va nix-devshell
Flake reference to a Nix devshell.
When set, the effective command becomes:
.Dl nix develop Ar ref Li --command Ar command args ...
.Pp
See
.Sx NIX DEVSHELL
below.
.El
.Sh COMMAND FORMAT
The
.Va command
field accepts two forms.
.Pp
String form (split on whitespace):
.Bd -literal -offset indent
command = "grit mcp --verbose"
.Ed
.Pp
Array form (preserved as-is):
.Bd -literal -offset indent
command = ["grit", "mcp", "--verbose"]
.Ed
.Pp
The first element is the executable; remaining elements are arguments.
Empty commands are invalid.
.Sh ANNOTATIONS
Annotation filters restrict which tools are exposed from a child server
based on MCP tool annotation hints.
They can be specified as a sub-table or as flat fields at the server level.
.Pp
Sub-table form:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[servers]]
name = "grit"
command = "grit mcp"

[servers.annotations]
readOnlyHint = true
.Ed
.Pp
Flat form:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[servers]]
name = "grit"
command = "grit mcp"
readOnlyHint = true
.Ed
.Pp
Available annotation fields:
.Bl -tag -width "destructiveHint"
.It Va readOnlyHint
Only expose tools marked as read-only.
.It Va destructiveHint
Only expose tools marked as destructive.
.It Va idempotentHint
Only expose tools marked as idempotent.
.It Va openWorldHint
Only expose tools marked as open-world.
.El
.Pp
All annotation fields are optional.
When set, only tools whose annotations match the specified value are exposed.
.Sh NIX DEVSHELL
The
.Va nix-devshell
field wraps the server command inside a Nix development shell.
.Pp
Given:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[servers]]
name = "example"
command = "myserver --verbose"
nix-devshell = "github:org/repo"
.Ed
.Pp
The effective command becomes:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
nix develop github:org/repo --command myserver --verbose
.Ed
.Pp
Valid flake references include
.Dq \&.
(current directory),
.Dq github:org/repo ,
and
.Dq github:org/repo?dir=path/to/subflake .
.Sh EXAMPLES
Minimal configuration with a single server:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[servers]]
name = "grit"
command = "grit mcp"
.Ed
.Pp
Multiple servers with annotation filtering:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[servers]]
name = "grit"
command = "grit mcp"
paginate = true

[servers.annotations]
readOnlyHint = true

[[servers]]
name = "lux"
command = ["lux", "mcp"]
generate-resource-tools = true
.Ed
.Pp
Ephemeral servers spawned on demand:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
ephemeral = true

[[servers]]
name = "chix"
command = "chix serve"

[[servers]]
name = "grit"
command = "grit mcp"
ephemeral = false
.Ed
.Pp
In this example,
.Dq chix
inherits the global ephemeral setting while
.Dq grit
overrides it to stay persistent.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr moxy 1 ,
.Xr moxy-native 7 ,
.Xr toml 5
